# Filename Convention: kebab-case

## Rule

When creating new files or directories, use kebab-case naming:

- Use lowercase letters, numbers, and hyphens only
- No spaces, underscores, or camelCase/PascalCase
- Examples:
  - Correct: `product-card.tsx`, `user-settings-modal.ts`, `order-list-item.css`
  - Incorrect: `ProductCard.tsx`, `user_settings.ts`, `orderListItem.css`

## Rationale

Kebab-case filenames are consistent and avoid cross-platform casing pitfalls.

## Tips

- Convert separators to hyphens
- Lowercase all words
- Keep names descriptive and concise